==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Diatom
<hw>Di"a*tom</hw> <pr>(d⟦imac⟧`⟦adot⟧*t⟦ocr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>dia`tomos</grk> cut in two. See
<er>Diatomous</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>One of the
<fam>Diatomace⟦ae⟧</fam>, a family of minute unicellular Alg⟦ae⟧ having
a siliceous covering of great delicacy, each individual multiplying by
spontaneous division. By some authors diatoms are called
<altname>Bacillari⟦ae⟧</altname>, but this word is not in general
use.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A particle or atom endowed with the vital
principle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The individual is nothing. He is no more than the
<qex>diatom</qex>, the bit of protoplasm.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs. E. Lynn
Linton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>diatomaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
